Computing a first correlation between gender and wage, we find that males earn on average 0.474 log points
more than women. 

::: {#e6f7fa80 .cell execution_count=2}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit_base = pf.feols("log(wage) ~ gender", data=psid, vcov="hetero")
fit_base.summary()
```

